Package com.example.unus

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Card
    Object used to represent a playing card for this game.
    ChatLayout
    this is the global chat for the app.
    ConfirmationLayout  
    Friend  
    FriendRequestFragment
    This fragment will get all of the incoming friend requests and display them so that the user can decide to either accept or decline then
    GameFourPlayerFragment
    Fragment to be used for gameplay when a game has four players.
    GameLobbyFragment
    Fragment used to handle the pre-game lobby
    GameTwoPlayerFragment
    Fragment used for gameplay when a game has two players
    JoinLobbyFragment
    Fragment used when joining a lobby based on lobby code
    LeaderboardFragment
    This fragment displays the leaderboard leaderboards include both friend sections and global sections it displays stats based on what you selected, that can be either friend or global and games played or games won
    LogInScreenFragment
    First Fragment you see when opening a screen.
    MainActivity
    Main activity that fragments are run within.
    MainMenuFragment
    Fragment used for the primary navigation around the menu screens.
    SignUpScreenFragment
    A fragment designed to allow the user to create a new account if they do not currently have an account for the app.
    UserData
    Singleton class designed to store user data which is accessible to all activities and fragments
    UserProfileFragment
    This fragment displays the stats of the user along with the users friends, from here the user can navigate to the user Settings You can also navigate to the user search fragment and friend requests fragment you can also remove friends on this page
    UserSearchFragment
    This class handles searching for a user and either viewing their stats or sending them a friend request You can also accept friend requests here given that they have already sent you a request
    UserSettingsFragment
    This fragment displays the user settings, for now they include change username, change password and delete user but will most likely be expanded in the future Change user will permanently change the name of the current user logged in change password changes the password delete user will remove the user from the database
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    CardColor
    enum used to store the different options for the card's color
    CardRank
    enum used to store the different values/ranks of the playing cards
